result.execSummary:
The defendant Kendrick Lamour Terry II was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fourth Degree Sexual Assault, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant.

-  Court sets Restitution at $0  (zero)

As to Count 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve  9  months  in the House of Correction. 

Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for  12  MONTHS with the following conditions:
-  Mental Health evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment and/or therapy
-  Take all medications as prescribed
-  Seek/Maintain employment
-  No Contact Order with the victim
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the surcharge (if not already done so) during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
if confinement is served - DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at a rate (to be determined by DOC).

Appeal rights given.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Copy given to the defendant.

Defendant Kendrick Lamour Terry in court with Attorney Lori Ann Kuehn.  Erin Michelle Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  All parties appear in person.
Defendant is prepared to enter a plea.

As to Count  1:
Defendant advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties; waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of   NO CONTEST   and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the Complaint as a factual basis for judgment.  Court finds defendant guilty as charged in the  Criminal Complaint and orders a judgment of conviction be entered.

As to Count  2:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders Count  2    DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Parties are prepared to proceed to sentencing.
